  "details": "While waiting for the channel synchronization, Irssi may incorrectly\nfail to remove destroyed channels from the query list, resulting in use\nafter free conditions when updating the state later on (CVE-2017-15227).\n\nWhen installing themes with unterminated color formatting sequences,\nIrssi may access data beyond the end of the string. (CVE-2017-15228).\n\nCertain incorrectly formatted DCC CTCP messages could cause NULL pointer\ndereference (CVE-2017-15721).\n\nIn certain cases Irssi may fail to verify that a Safe channel ID is long\nenough, causing reads beyond the end of the string (CVE-2017-15722).\n\nOverlong nicks or targets may result in a NULL pointer dereference while\nsplitting the message (CVE-2017-15723).\n",
